.TH "install-todo" "1" "pilot-link - @VERSION@" "(c) FSF 1996-2003" "Conduits"
.SH "NAME"
\fBinstall\-todo\fR \- Updates the Palm ToDo list with one new entry

.SH "SYNOPSIS"
\fBinstall\-todo\fR [\fB\-p\fR <\fIport\fR>] [\fB\-P\fR <\fIpriority\fR>] [\fB\-d\fR <\fIduedate\fR>] [\fB\-c\fR] [\fB\-n\fR <\fInote\fR>] [\fB\-f\fR <\fIfilename\fR>]

.SH "DESCRIPTION"
\fBinstall\-todo\fR allows the user to install one new ToDo list entry with specified paramters passed to \fBinstall\-todo\fR and add a Note entry using text found in a filename <\fIfilename\fR> passed to \fBinstall\-todo\fR
.SH "OPTIONS"
.TP 
\fB\-p\fR, \fB\-\-port\fR <\fIport\fR>
Use device file <\fIport\fR> to communicate with the Palm handheld device. If this is not specified, will look for the \fI$PILOTPORT\fR environment variable. If both are not found, will fall back to /dev/pilot


.TP 
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Display help synopsis for \fBinstall\-hinote\fR


.TP 
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Display version of \fBinstall\-hinote\fR


.TP 
\fB\-P\fR, \fB\-\-priority\fR <\fIpriority\fR>
Specify the priority of the ToDo entry (defaults to 4)


.TP 
\fB\-d\fR, \fB\-\-due\fR <\fIduedate\fR>
The due Date MM/DD/YYYY (defaults to blank, no due date)


.TP 
\fB\-c\fR, \fB\-\-completed\fR
Mark the item complete (default is incomplete)


.TP 
\fB\-n\fR, \fB\-\-note\fR <\fInote\fR>
The Note text you wish to add to this ToDo entry


.TP 
\fB\-f\fR, \fB\-\-file\fR <\fIfilename\fR>
A local filename containing the Note text
.SH "USAGE"
The program will connect to a target Palm handheld device, and writes the
ToDo entry to the Palm ToDo List application, using the specified parameters and input from the supplied file passed as arguments
